 {
   "topic": "Cloud concepts",
   "quizTitle": "Benefits of using cloud services",
   "questions": [
     {
       "questionType": "multi-choice",
       "difficulty": "medium",
       "points": 1,
       "translations": [
         {
           "languageCode": "en",
           "questionText": "Which features does Azure provide to enhance the reliability of\napplications? (Select all that apply)",
           "options": {
             "option_1": "Built-in data replication across availability zones and regions",
             "option_2": "Placement of managed disks in different storage scale units",
             "option_3": "Spreading virtual machines across fault domains",
             "option_4": "Automatic transition between availability zones without interruption"
           },
           "correctAnswer": [
             "option_1",
             "option_2",
             "option_3",
             "option_4"
           ],
           "explanation": "Azure provides several features to enhance the reliability of applications:\n\na) Built-in data replication across availability zones and regions: Azure\noffers built-in replication capabilities that allow data to be replicated\nacross different availability zones within a region or even across regions.\nThis helps ensure that data remains available and accessible even in the\nevent of a failure in one zone or region.\n\nb) Placement of managed disks in different storage scale units: Azure\nallows for the placement of managed disks in different storage scale units.\nBy distributing the disks across different scale units, the risk of a single\npoint of failure is reduced, enhancing the reliability of the application.\n\nc) Spreading virtual machines across fault domains: Azure enables the\nspreading of virtual machines (VMs) across fault domains. Fault domains\nare logical groupings of resources that are isolated from one another. By\nspreading VMs across fault domains, the impact of a failure on a single\ndomain is limited, ensuring the availability of applications.\n\nd) Automatic transition between availability zones without interruption:\nAzure provides the capability for automatic transition between availability\nzones without interruption. This means that if an outage occurs in one\navailability zone, Azure can seamlessly transition the workload to another\navailability zone without causing disruptions or interruptions.\n\nTherefore, the correct answers are a) Built-in data replication across\navailability zones and regions, b) Placement of managed disks in different\nstorage scale units, c) Spreading virtual machines across fault domains,\nand d) Automatic transition between availability zones without\ninterruption."
         }
       ]
     },
     {
       "questionType": "single-choice",
       "difficulty": "medium",
       "points": 1,
       "translations": [
         {
           "languageCode": "en",
           "questionText": "What should be considered when designing an application to be resilient?",
           "options": {
             "option_1": "Cost of downtime and investment in high availability",
             "option_2": "Preventing any disruptions or failures in the entire region",
             "option_3": "Minimizing network congestion and transient problems",
             "option_4": "Root causes of failures and monitoring diagnostics"
           },
           "correctAnswer": [
             "option_1"
           ],
           "explanation": "When designing an application to be resilient, several factors should be\nconsidered.\n\na) Cost of downtime and investment in high availability: It is essential to\nconsider the cost of downtime and determine the level of investment\nrequired to achieve high availability. This involves analyzing the impact\nof system failures, evaluating the potential financial losses during\ndowntime, and making informed decisions on investing in redundancy,\nfault tolerance, and disaster recovery mechanisms.\n\nb) Preventing any disruptions or failures in the entire region: While\npreventing disruptions or failures in the entire region is desirable, it may\nnot always be feasible or necessary for every application. Resilient\napplication design focuses on minimizing the impact of failures on\napplication availability and maintaining an acceptable level of service,\nrather than completely eliminating all failures across the entire region.\n\nc) Minimizing network congestion and transient problems: Minimizing\nnetwork congestion and addressing transient problems is a consideration\nfor optimizing application performance and reliability, but it is not the sole\naspect of designing for resiliency.\n\nd) Root causes of failures and monitoring diagnostics: Understanding and\naddressing the root causes of failures is an important part of designing\nresilient applications. Monitoring diagnostics and implementing proactive\nmeasures to detect and mitigate potential failure points can enhance\nresilience.\n\nConsidering all the options, the most critical factor to consider when\ndesigning resilient applications is the cost of downtime and making\nappropriate investments in high availability. Therefore, the correct answer\nis a) Cost of downtime and investment in high availability."
         }
       ]
     }
   ]
